{"TopicId":146178,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"I can\u0026#039;t land at Mars need help (RSS\u002BRO)","CreatedByName":"berkekrkn","CreatedById":156179,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-19T14:34:39Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"berkekrkn","CreatedById":156179,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-19T14:34:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi guys,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI start to build Mars Transfer Vehicle but first I need to design a lander. The atmosphere of Mars is really thin. I enter the atmosphere with 3200 m/s and it decelerates me to 2800m/s. I can\u0027t open the chutes btw. the vessel has 40 tonns of mass, so the chutes are useless.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI enter the atmoshphere with 7.5 meters shield(not inflatable heatshield rather normal). Even it is useless.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor departure from Mars\u00A0I need to reserve 3.800 delta V fuel.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1-) Is there a solution ? If not should I use some more fuel for stopping the vessel?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut then the mass of the vessel will increase to 50 tonns even I am using lh2 and lox propellant.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-19T14:35:41Z\u0022 title=\u002208/19/2016 02:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 19, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by berkekrkn\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Optimist","CreatedById":151904,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-19T14:36:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you considered that maybe you\u0027re reentering at too steep an angle?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"berkekrkn","CreatedById":156179,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-19T14:37:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222722322\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146178\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471617376\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022151904\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Optimist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, The Optimist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you considered that maybe you\u0027re reentering at too steep an angle?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI keep periapsis at \u002B20,000 - \u002B40,000 \u00A0meters. Also I try to waste as much time as I can in the atmosphere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Optimist","CreatedById":151904,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-19T14:38:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222722324\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146178\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471617450\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156179\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022berkekrkn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, berkekrkn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI keep periapsis at \u002B20,000 - \u002B40,000 \u00A0meters. Also I try to waste as much time as I can in the atmosphere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWay too steep, \u00A0try to keep the periapsis above 50K\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"berkekrkn","CreatedById":156179,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-19T16:02:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222722326\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146178\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471617502\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022151904\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Optimist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, The Optimist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWay too steep, \u00A0try to keep the periapsis above 50K\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk thanks, I did some test and it is getting better now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}